    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>B-Tree Index Interactive Demo</title>\n<style>\n/* Extremely minimal plain styling: black text on white background, basic layout only */\nhtml,body { margin:10px; padding:10px; font-family: monospace; color: #000; background: #fff; }\nsection { margin-bottom:12px; padding:6px; border:1px solid #000; }\nbutton,input,select,textarea { margin:2px 4px 2px 0; }\nlabel { margin-right:8px; }\nsmall { display:block; margin-top:4px; color: #000; }\npre { white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>B-Tree Index — Interactive Demo</h2>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Tree Configuration</strong><br>\n  <label>Minimum degree (t): <input id=\"tInput\" type=\"number\" min=\"2\" max=\"10\" value=\"2\" style=\"width:50px\"></label>\n  <label>Derived max keys per node: <span id=\"maxKeysLabel\">3</span></label>\n  <label>Key type:\n    <select id=\"keyType\">\n      <option value=\"number\">Number</option>\n      <option value=\"string\">String</option>\n    </select>\n  </label>\n  <button id=\"reinitBtn\">Reinitialize Tree</button>\n  <small>Minimum degree t defines the B-Tree properties. Max keys per node = 2*t - 1.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Single Operations</strong><br>\n  <label>Key to insert: <input id=\"insertKey\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:120px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"insertBtn\">Insert</button>\n  <button id=\"insertStepBtn\">Insert (Step Mode)</button>\n  <label>Key to delete: <input id=\"deleteKey\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:120px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"deleteBtn\">Delete</button>\n  <button id=\"deleteStepBtn\">Delete (Step Mode)</button>\n  <label>Search: <input id=\"searchKey\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:120px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"searchBtn\">Search</button>\n  <small>Supports numeric and string keys. Use Step Mode to see algorithmic transitions.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Bulk & Random Operations</strong><br>\n  <label>Bulk insert (comma separated):</label><br>\n  <input id=\"bulkInsert\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:60%\" placeholder=\"e.g. 10,4,6,23,17\">\n  <button id=\"bulkInsertBtn\">Bulk Insert</button>\n  <button id=\"clearBtn\">Clear Tree</button>\n  <br>\n  <label>Random insert count: <input id=\"randCount\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" max=\"200\" value=\"10\" style=\"width:60px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"randInsertBtn\">Random Insert</button>\n  <small>Random inserts generate numbers in range 0..999 (or strings 'sNN').</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Range & Scan</strong><br>\n  <label>Range low: <input id=\"rangeLow\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:80px\"></label>\n  <label>Range high: <input id=\"rangeHigh\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:80px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"rangeBtn\">Range Query</button>\n  <button id=\"traverseBtn\">Full In-order Traversal</button>\n  <small>Range and traversal results printed to the log area. Inclusive range.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Stepper / Playback</strong><br>\n  <button id=\"prevStep\">Prev Step</button>\n  <button id=\"nextStep\">Next Step</button>\n  <button id=\"autoPlay\">Auto Play</button>\n  <button id=\"pausePlay\">Pause</button>\n  <label>Speed (ms): <input id=\"speed\" type=\"number\" min=\"50\" max=\"2000\" value=\"600\" style=\"width:80px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"resetSteps\">Reset Step Session</button>\n  <small>Use Step Mode on operations to generate an algorithmic trace you can step through. History is recorded to allow undo/redo.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Manual Node Operations & Editor</strong><br>\n  <label>Node ID: <input id=\"nodeIdInput\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:80px\"></label>\n  <button id=\"splitNodeBtn\">Manual Split Node</button>\n  <button id=\"mergeNodeBtn\">Manual Merge With Right Sibling</button>\n  <button id=\"borrowLeftBtn\">Borrow From Left Sibling</button>\n  <button id=\"borrowRightBtn\">Borrow From Right Sibling</button>\n  <button id=\"editNodeBtn\">Open Node Editor</button>\n  <div id=\"nodeEditor\" style=\"display:none; margin-top:6px;\">\n    <label>Keys (comma separated): <input id=\"nodeKeys\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:50%\"></label><br>\n    <label>Children IDs (comma separated or empty): <input id=\"nodeChildren\" type=\"text\" style=\"width:50%\"></label><br>\n    <label>Leaf: <input id=\"nodeLeaf\" type=\"checkbox\"></label>\n    <button id=\"applyNodeEdit\">Apply Changes</button>\n    <button id=\"closeNodeEditor\">Close Editor</button>\n  </div>\n  <small>Manual operations can break invariants; use Validate button to check consistency. IDs are assigned internally.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Export / Import / Undo</strong><br>\n  <button id=\"exportBtn\">Export JSON (Copy)</button>\n  <button id=\"importBtn\">Import JSON (Paste)</button>\n  <button id=\"undoBtn\">Undo</button>\n  <button id=\"redoBtn\">Redo</button>\n  <input id=\"importArea\" type=\"file\" style=\"display:inline-block\">\n  <small>Export copies the current structure as JSON to a text box. Import accepts JSON to replace tree. Undo/Redo available.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Diagnostics & Controls</strong><br>\n  <button id=\"validateBtn\">Validate Invariants</button>\n  <button id=\"statsBtn\">Show Stats</button>\n  <button id=\"compactBtn\">Rebuild / Compact Tree (reinsert keys)</button>\n  <button id=\"showPagesBtn\">Show Disk Page Simulation</button>\n  <small>Use validate to ensure basic B-Tree properties hold. Compact rebuilds tree by reinserting keys in-order.</small>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Tree View (click node IDs to edit)</strong>\n  <pre id=\"treeView\">(empty)</pre>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <strong>Operation Log</strong>\n  <textarea id=\"logArea\" rows=\"12\" style=\"width:100%\"></textarea>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n// B-Tree implementation with interactive stepping, history, and many controls.\n// Uses classic min-degree t definition: max keys = 2*t - 1, min keys = t - 1.\n\n// Utility: simple ID generator for nodes\nlet nextNodeId = 1;\nfunction newNodeId(){ return nextNodeId++; }\n\n// Compare function respecting key type choice\nfunction makeComparator(isNumeric) {\n  return function(a,b){\n    if(isNumeric){\n      const na = parseFloat(a);\n      const nb = parseFloat(b);\n      if(!isFinite(na) || !isFinite(nb)){\n        // fallback to string compare\n        return String(a) < String(b) ? -1 : (String(a) > String(b) ? 1 : 0);\n      }\n      return na - nb;\n    } else {\n      if(String(a) < String(b)) return -1;\n      if(String(a) > String(b)) return 1;\n      return 0;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Node constructor\nfunction BNode(leaf=false){\n  this.id = newNodeId();\n  this.keys = []; // array of keys\n  this.children = []; // array of child nodes\n  this.leaf = !!leaf;\n}\n\n// Deep clone node (helper)\nfunction cloneNode(node){\n  const n = new BNode(node.leaf);\n  n.id = node.id; // preserve id for easier mapping\n  n.keys = node.keys.slice();\n  n.children = node.children.slice();\n  return n;\n}\n\n// BTree class\nfunction BTree(minDegree, comparator){\n  this.t = minDegree; // min degree\n  this.compare = comparator;\n  this.root = new BNode(true);\n  this._log = [];\n}\n\nBTree.prototype.cloneStructure = function(nodeMap){\n  // produce a serializable representation with node ids and references\n  const nodes = [];\n  const visited = new Map();\n  function dfs(n){\n    if(visited.has(n.id)) return;\n    visited.set(n.id, true);\n    nodes.push({\n      id: n.id,\n      keys: n.keys.slice(),\n      leaf: n.leaf,\n      children: n.children.map(c => c.id)\n    });\n    n.children.forEach(child => dfs(child));\n  }\n  dfs(this.root);\n  return {t: this.t, nodes: nodes, rootId: this.root.id};\n};\n\nBTree.prototype.toJSON = function(){\n  return JSON.stringify(this.cloneStructure(), null, 2);\n};\n\nBTree.prototype.fromJSON = function(json){\n  // reconstruct tree from serialized nodes mapping\n  const obj = (typeof json === 'string') ? JSON.parse(json) : json;\n  if(!obj || !obj.nodes) throw new Error(\"Invalid JSON\");\n  this.t = obj.t;\n  const map = new Map();\n  obj.nodes.forEach(n => {\n    const nd = new BNode(!!n.leaf);\n    nd.id = n.id;\n    nd.keys = n.keys.slice();\n    nd.children = [];\n    map.set(nd.id, nd);\n  });\n  obj.nodes.forEach(n => {\n    const nd = map.get(n.id);\n    nd.children = n.children.map(cid => {\n      const child = map.get(cid);\n      if(!child) throw new Error(\"Invalid child link\");\n      return child;\n    });\n  });\n  if(!map.has(obj.rootId)) throw new Error(\"Invalid root id\");\n  this.root = map.get(obj.rootId);\n};\n\n// Basic utilities\nBTree.prototype.traverse = function(node, result){\n  if(!node) return;\n  for(let i=0;i<node.keys.length;i++){\n    if(!node.leaf) this.traverse(node.children[i], result);\n    result.push(node.keys[i]);\n  }\n  if(!node.leaf) this.traverse(node.children[node.keys.length], result);\n};\n\nBTree.prototype.rangeQuery = function(low, high){\n  const res = [];\n  function rec(n){\n    if(!n) return;\n    for(let i=0;i<n.keys.length;i++){\n      if(!n.leaf) rec(n.children[i]);\n      const key = n.keys[i];\n      if((low===null || this.compare(key,low)>=0) && (high===null || this.compare(key,high)<=0)){\n        res.push(key);\n      }\n    }\n    if(!n.leaf) rec(n.children[n.keys.length]);\n  }\n  rec = rec.bind(this);\n  rec(this.root);\n  return res;\n};\n\nBTree.prototype.search = function(key){\n  function rec(n){\n    let i=0;\n    while(i < n.keys.length && this.compare(key,n.keys[i]) > 0) i++;\n    if(i < n.keys.length && this.compare(key,n.keys[i])===0) return {node: n, index: i};\n    if(n.leaf) return null;\n    return rec.call(this, n.children[i]);\n  }\n  return rec.call(this, this.root);\n};\n\n// Insertion (standard CLRS algorithm) with step capturing\nBTree.prototype.insert = function(key, captureSteps){\n  if(captureSteps) {\n    const steps = [];\n    steps.push({message: \"Start insert of key \" + key, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    const result = this._insertWithSteps(key, steps);\n    steps.push({message: \"Insert complete. Final tree state.\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    return steps;\n  } else {\n    return this._insertNoSteps(key);\n  }\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._insertNoSteps = function(key){\n  const r = this.root;\n  if(r.keys.length === 2*this.t - 1){\n    const s = new BNode(false);\n    s.children.push(r);\n    this.root = s;\n    this._splitChild(s,0);\n    this._insertNonFull(s, key);\n  } else {\n    this._insertNonFull(r, key);\n  }\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._insertWithSteps = function(key, steps){\n  const r = this.root;\n  if(r.keys.length === 2*this.t - 1){\n    steps.push({message: \"Root is full; splitting root\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    const s = new BNode(false);\n    s.children.push(r);\n    this.root = s;\n    this._splitChildWithSteps(s,0, steps);\n    steps.push({message: \"Proceed to insert into non-full node\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    this._insertNonFullWithSteps(s, key, steps);\n  } else {\n    this._insertNonFullWithSteps(r, key, steps);\n  }\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._insertNonFull = function(node, key){\n  let i = node.keys.length - 1;\n  if(node.leaf){\n    // insert key in place\n    while(i >= 0 && this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) < 0){\n      i--;\n    }\n    node.keys.splice(i+1,0,key);\n  } else {\n    while(i >= 0 && this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) < 0) i--;\n    i++;\n    if(node.children[i].keys.length === 2*this.t -1){\n      this._splitChild(node, i);\n      if(this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) > 0) i++;\n    }\n    this._insertNonFull(node.children[i], key);\n  }\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._insertNonFullWithSteps = function(node, key, steps){\n  let i = node.keys.length - 1;\n  if(node.leaf){\n    steps.push({message: \"Inserting into leaf node id=\"+node.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    while(i >= 0 && this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) < 0) i--;\n    node.keys.splice(i+1,0,key);\n    steps.push({message: \"Inserted key into leaf id=\"+node.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n  } else {\n    while(i >= 0 && this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) < 0) i--;\n    i++;\n    steps.push({message: \"Descending into child index \"+i+\" (node id=\"+node.children[i].id+\")\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    if(node.children[i].keys.length === 2*this.t -1){\n      steps.push({message: \"Child is full; splitting child id=\"+node.children[i].id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n      this._splitChildWithSteps(node, i, steps);\n      steps.push({message: \"After split, current node state\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n      if(this.compare(key, node.keys[i]) > 0) i++;\n    }\n    this._insertNonFullWithSteps(node.children[i], key, steps);\n  }\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._splitChild = function(parent, i){\n  const y = parent.children[i];\n  const z = new BNode(y.leaf);\n  // y has 2t-1 keys; split into y with t-1 keys and z with t-1 keys, median promoted\n  const t = this.t;\n  // median index = t-1\n  z.keys = y.keys.splice(t); // keys from index t..end\n  const median = y.keys.splice(t-1,1)[0]; // remove median from y\n  if(!y.leaf){\n    z.children = y.children.splice(t); // children from t..end\n  }\n  parent.children.splice(i+1,0,z);\n  parent.keys.splice(i,0,median);\n};\n\nBTree.prototype._splitChildWithSteps = function(parent, i, steps){\n  const y = parent.children[i];\n  const z = new BNode(y.leaf);\n  const t = this.t;\n  z.keys = y.keys.splice(t);\n  const median = y.keys.splice(t-1,1)[0];\n  if(!y.leaf){\n    z.children = y.children.splice(t);\n  }\n  parent.children.splice(i+1,0,z);\n  parent.keys.splice(i,0,median);\n  steps.push({message: \"Split node id=\"+y.id+\" into nodes id=\"+y.id+\" and id=\"+z.id+\" with median promoted\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n};\n\n// Deletion (CLRS algorithm). Returns steps if captureSteps true.\nBTree.prototype.delete = function(key, captureSteps){\n  if(captureSteps){\n    const steps = [];\n    steps.push({message: \"Start delete of key \" + key, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    this._deleteWithSteps(this.root, key, steps);\n    // adjust root\n    if(this.root.keys.length === 0 && !this.root.leaf){\n      this.root = this.root.children[0];\n      steps.push({message: \"Root had 0 keys; new root is child\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    }\n    steps.push({message: \"Delete complete\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n    return steps;\n  } else {\n    this._deleteNoSteps(this.root, key);\n    if(this.root.keys.length === 0 && !this.root.leaf) this.root = this.root.children[0];\n  }\n};\n\n// Non-step delete wrapper\nBTree.prototype._deleteNoSteps = function(node, key){\n  this._deleteWithSteps(node, key, null);\n};\n\n// Core deletion algorithm with optional steps capturing\nBTree.prototype._deleteWithSteps = function(x, k, steps){\n  const t = this.t;\n  const cmp = this.compare;\n  let i = 0;\n  while(i < x.keys.length && cmp(k, x.keys[i]) > 0) i++;\n  if(i < x.keys.length && cmp(k, x.keys[i]) === 0){\n    // case 1: k is in node x\n    if(x.leaf){\n      // Case 1a: x is leaf -> remove key\n      if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Key found in leaf node id=\"+x.id+\"; removing directly\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n      x.keys.splice(i,1);\n      return;\n    } else {\n      // x is internal\n      const predChild = x.children[i];\n      const succChild = x.children[i+1];\n      if(predChild.keys.length >= t){\n        // find predecessor\n        let cur = predChild;\n        while(!cur.leaf) cur = cur.children[cur.keys.length];\n        const predKey = cur.keys[cur.keys.length-1];\n        if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Key found in internal node id=\"+x.id+\"; predecessor available in child id=\"+predChild.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n        x.keys[i] = predKey;\n        this._deleteWithSteps(predChild, predKey, steps);\n        return;\n      } else if(succChild.keys.length >= t){\n        let cur = succChild;\n        while(!cur.leaf) cur = cur.children[0];\n        const succKey = cur.keys[0];\n        if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Key found in internal node id=\"+x.id+\"; successor available in child id=\"+succChild.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n        x.keys[i] = succKey;\n        this._deleteWithSteps(succChild, succKey, steps);\n        return;\n      } else {\n        // merge k and succChild into predChild\n        if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Merging children id=\"+predChild.id+\" and id=\"+succChild.id+\" with key from parent\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n        // move k down\n        predChild.keys.push(x.keys[i]);\n        predChild.keys = predChild.keys.concat(succChild.keys);\n        if(!predChild.leaf) predChild.children = predChild.children.concat(succChild.children);\n        // remove succChild and key from parent\n        x.keys.splice(i,1);\n        x.children.splice(i+1,1);\n        this._deleteWithSteps(predChild, k, steps);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n  } else {\n    // case 2: k not present in internal node x\n    if(x.leaf){\n      if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Key not found; reached leaf id=\"+x.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n      return; // key not found\n    }\n    // Determine child index to descend\n    let childIndex = i;\n    let child = x.children[childIndex];\n    // If child has t-1 keys, need to fill\n    if(child.keys.length < t){\n      // if left sibling has >= t keys, borrow\n      const leftSibling = childIndex - 1 >= 0 ? x.children[childIndex-1] : null;\n      const rightSibling = childIndex + 1 < x.children.length ? x.children[childIndex+1] : null;\n      if(leftSibling && leftSibling.keys.length >= t){\n        if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Borrowing from left sibling id=\"+leftSibling.id+\" into child id=\"+child.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n        // move key from parent down, move key from left sibling up\n        child.keys.unshift(x.keys[childIndex-1]);\n        if(!leftSibling.leaf){\n          child.children.unshift(leftSibling.children.pop());\n        }\n        x.keys[childIndex-1] = leftSibling.keys.pop();\n      } else if(rightSibling && rightSibling.keys.length >= t){\n        if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Borrowing from right sibling id=\"+rightSibling.id+\" into child id=\"+child.id, snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n        child.keys.push(x.keys[childIndex]);\n        if(!rightSibling.leaf){\n          child.children.push(rightSibling.children.shift());\n        }\n        x.keys[childIndex] = rightSibling.keys.shift();\n      } else {\n        // merge child with a sibling\n        if(leftSibling){\n          if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Merging child id=\"+leftSibling.id+\" and id=\"+child.id+\" because both have minimum keys\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n          // move key from parent down into leftSibling\n          leftSibling.keys.push(x.keys[childIndex-1]);\n          leftSibling.keys = leftSibling.keys.concat(child.keys);\n          if(!child.leaf) leftSibling.children = leftSibling.children.concat(child.children);\n          x.keys.splice(childIndex-1,1);\n          x.children.splice(childIndex,1);\n          child = leftSibling;\n        } else if(rightSibling){\n          if(steps) steps.push({message: \"Merging child id=\"+child.id+\" and id=\"+rightSibling.id+\" because both have minimum keys\", snapshot: this.cloneStructure()});\n          child.keys.push(x.keys[childIndex]);\n          child.keys = child.keys.concat(rightSibling.keys);\n          if(!rightSibling.leaf) child.children = child.children.concat(rightSibling.children);\n          x.keys.splice(childIndex,1);\n          x.children.splice(childIndex+1,1);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    // After ensuring child has at least t keys, recurse\n    // But child may have changed reference if merged; determine correct child to descend\n    if(childIndex >= x.children.length) childIndex = x.children.length-1;\n    this._deleteWithSteps(x.children[childIndex], k, steps);\n    return;\n  }\n};\n\n// Validate invariants: returns list of issues or empty\nBTree.prototype.validate = function(){\n  const issues = [];\n  const t = this.t;\n  let root = this.root;\n  // compute height by following leftmost path\n  let height = 0;\n  let cur = root;\n  while(cur && !cur.leaf){ height++; cur = cur.children[0]; }\n  // Validate recursively\n  function rec(node, level){\n    if(node.keys.length > 2*t -1) issues.push(\"Node id=\"+node.id+\" has > max keys: \"+node.keys.length);\n    if(node !== root && node.keys.length < t-1) issues.push(\"Node id=\"+node.id+\" has < min keys: \"+node.keys.length);\n    // keys sorted?\n    for(let i=1;i<node.keys.length;i++){\n      if(node.keys[i-1] > node.keys[i]) issues.push(\"Node id=\"+node.id+\" has unsorted keys order\");\n    }\n    if(!node.leaf){\n      if(node.children.length !== node.keys.length+1) issues.push(\"Internal node id=\"+node.id+\" children count mismatch\");\n      // check key separation between children\n      for(let i=0;i<node.keys.length;i++){\n        const maxLeft = maxKey(node.children[i]);\n        const minRight = minKey(node.children[i+1]);\n        if(maxLeft === null || minRight === null) continue;\n        if(!(maxLeft <= node.keys[i] && node.keys[i] <= minRight)) issues.push(\"Key separation violation near node id=\"+node.id+\" keyIndex=\"+i);\n      }\n      node.children.forEach(c => rec(c, level+1));\n    } else {\n      if(node.children.length !== 0) issues.push(\"Leaf node id=\"+node.id+\" has children\");\n    }\n  }\n  function minKey(node){\n    if(!node) return null;\n    let cur=node;\n    while(!cur.leaf) cur = cur.children[0];\n    return cur.keys[0];\n  }\n  function maxKey(node){\n    if(!node) return null;\n    let cur=node;\n    while(!cur.leaf) cur = cur.children[cur.keys.length];\n    return cur.keys[cur.keys.length-1];\n  }\n  rec(root, 0);\n  return issues;\n};\n\n// Utility to collect stats\nBTree.prototype.stats = function(){\n  let nodes=0, keys=0, leafCount=0;\n  function rec(n, depth, depthCounts){\n    nodes++;\n    keys += n.keys.length;\n    if(n.leaf) leafCount++;\n    n.children.forEach(c => rec(c, depth+1, depthCounts));\n  }\n  rec(this.root, 0, {});\n  return {nodes: nodes, keys: keys, leafCount: leafCount, t: this.t};\n};\n\n// Manual operations helpers: find node by id\nBTree.prototype.findNodeById = function(id){\n  let found = null;\n  function rec(n){\n    if(n.id === id) { found = n; return; }\n    if(!n.leaf){\n      for(let c of n.children){ if(found) return; rec(c); }\n    }\n  }\n  rec(this.root);\n  return found;\n};\n\n// Manual split: split node if possible (similar to splitChild but split parent must be found)\nBTree.prototype.manualSplitNode = function(nodeId){\n  // Find parent and node index\n  let parent = null;\n  let index = -1;\n  function rec(n){\n    for(let i=0;i<n.children.length;i++){\n      if(n.children[i].id === nodeId){ parent = n; index = i; return true; }\n      if(!n.children[i].leaf) if(rec(n.children[i])) return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n  if(this.root.id === nodeId) return {ok:false, message:\"Cannot manually split root via this operation. Use reinit or programmatic split during insert.\"};\n  if(!rec(this.root)) return {ok:false, message:\"Parent not found for node id=\"+nodeId};\n  const child = parent.children[index];\n  if(child.keys.length < 2*this.t -1) return {ok:false, message:\"Node not full; manual split usually applied to full nodes.\"};\n  this._splitChild(parent, index);\n  return {ok:true, message:\"Node split applied at parent id=\"+parent.id};\n};\n\n// Manual merge operation: merge node with right sibling at parent\nBTree.prototype.manualMergeWithRight = function(nodeId){\n  // find parent where children[i].id == nodeId and exists children[i+1]\n  let parent = null, idx=-1;\n  function rec(n){\n    for(let i=0;i<n.children.length;i++){\n      if(n.children[i].id === nodeId){ parent = n; idx = i; return true; }\n      if(!n.children[i].leaf) if(rec(n.children[i])) return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n  if(!rec(this.root)) return {ok:false, message:\"Parent not found\"};\n  if(idx+1 >= parent.children.length) return {ok:false, message:\"No right sibling to merge with\"};\n  const left = parent.children[idx], right = parent.children[idx+1];\n  left.keys.push(parent.keys[idx]);\n  left.keys = left.keys.concat(right.keys);\n  if(!left.leaf) left.children = left.children.concat(right.children);\n  parent.keys.splice(idx,1);\n  parent.children.splice(idx+1,1);\n  if(parent === this.root && parent.keys.length === 0) this.root = left;\n  return {ok:true, message:\"Merged node id=\"+left.id+\" with right sibling id=\"+right.id};\n};\n\n// Borrow helpers\nBTree.prototype.manualBorrowFromLeft = function(nodeId){\n  // find parent and index\n  let parent=null, idx=-1;\n  function rec(n){\n    for(let i=0;i<n.children.length;i++){\n      if(n.children[i].id === nodeId){ parent=n; idx=i; return true; }\n      if(!n.children[i].leaf) if(rec(n.children[i])) return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n  if(!rec(this.root)) return {ok:false, message:\"Parent not found\"};\n  if(idx-1 < 0) return {ok:false, message:\"No left sibling\"};\n  const child = parent.children[idx], left = parent.children[idx-1];\n  if(left.keys.length === 0) return {ok:false, message:\"Left sibling empty\"};\n  // move parent's key down and left's top key up\n  child.keys.unshift(parent.keys[idx-1]);\n  parent.keys[idx-1] = left.keys.pop();\n  if(!left.leaf) child.children.unshift(left.children.pop());\n  return {ok:true, message:\"Borrowed from left sibling id=\"+left.id+\" into node id=\"+child.id};\n};\n\nBTree.prototype.manualBorrowFromRight = function(nodeId){\n  let parent=null, idx=-1;\n  function rec(n){\n    for(let i=0;i<n.children.length;i++){\n      if(n.children[i].id === nodeId){ parent=n; idx=i; return true; }\n      if(!n.children[i].leaf) if(rec(n.children[i])) return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n  if(!rec(this.root)) return {ok:false, message:\"Parent not found\"};\n  if(idx+1 >= parent.children.length) return {ok:false, message:\"No right sibling\"};\n  const child = parent.children[idx], right = parent.children[idx+1];\n  if(right.keys.length === 0) return {ok:false, message:\"Right sibling empty\"};\n  child.keys.push(parent.keys[idx]);\n  parent.keys[idx] = right.keys.shift();\n  if(!right.leaf) child.children.push(right.children.shift());\n  return {ok:true, message:\"Borrowed from right sibling id=\"+right.id+\" into node id=\"+child.id};\n};\n\n// Rebuild / compact by reinserting keys in-order\nBTree.prototype.rebuild = function(){\n  const keys=[];\n  this.traverse(this.root, keys);\n  // create new empty tree\n  const t = this.t;\n  nextNodeId = 1;\n  this.root = new BNode(true);\n  for(const k of keys) this._insertNoSteps(k);\n};\n\n// Disk page simulation\nBTree.prototype.diskPages = function(maxKeysPerPage){\n  const pages = [];\n  let pageId = 1;\n  // traverse nodes and pack keys into pages sequentially\n  function rec(node){\n    const items = [];\n    // represent node keys as one \"page item\"\n    const repr = {nodeId: node.id, keys: node.keys.slice(), leaf: node.leaf};\n    pages.push({pageId: pageId++, node: repr});\n    node.children.forEach(c => rec(c));\n  }\n  rec(this.root);\n  return pages;\n};\n\n// ---------- UI & Interaction Logic ----------\n\nconst logArea = document.getElementById('logArea');\nfunction log(msg){\n  const time = new Date().toLocaleTimeString();\n  logArea.value += \"[\"+time+\"] \"+msg+\"\\n\";\n  logArea.scrollTop = logArea.scrollHeight;\n}\n\n// Global tree instance\nlet comparator = makeComparator(true);\nlet tree = new BTree(2, comparator);\nlet history = [];\nlet future = [];\n\n// Stepper state\nlet currentSteps = null;\nlet currentStepIndex = -1;\nlet autoplayTimer = null;\n\nfunction pushHistory(actionDescription){\n  try {\n    const snapshot = tree.cloneStructure();\n    history.push(snapshot);\n    future = [];\n    document.getElementById('undoBtn').disabled = false;\n    document.getElementById('redoBtn').disabled = true;\n    log(\"Saved state to history: \" + actionDescription);\n  } catch(e){\n    console.error(e);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction restoreSnapshot(snapshot){\n  tree.fromJSON(snapshot);\n}\n\nfunction updateConfigurationUI(){\n  const tVal = parseInt(document.getElementById('tInput').value,10) || 2;\n  document.getElementById('maxKeysLabel').innerText = (2*tVal - 1).toString();\n}\n\ndocument.getElementById('tInput').addEventListener('change', function(){\n  updateConfigurationUI();\n});\n\ndocument.getElementById('reinitBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const tVal = Math.max(2, parseInt(document.getElementById('tInput').value,10) || 2);\n  const keyType = document.getElementById('keyType').value;\n  comparator = makeComparator(keyType === 'number');\n  tree = new BTree(tVal, comparator);\n  history = [];\n  future = [];\n  nextNodeId = 1;\n  renderTree();\n  log(\"Initialized new B-Tree with t=\"+tVal+\" keyType=\"+keyType);\n});\n\nfunction renderTree(){\n  const pre = document.getElementById('treeView');\n  if(!tree.root || (tree.root.keys.length===0 && tree.root.leaf)) {\n    pre.textContent = \"(empty)\";\n    return;\n  }\n  // pretty textual print: level-order with node id and keys\n  const lines = [];\n  function rec(node, indent){\n    lines.push(\" \".repeat(indent) + \"Node id=\"+node.id + \" | keys=[\"+node.keys.join(\", \")+\"]\" + (node.leaf? \" leaf\": \"\"));\n    node.children.forEach(c => rec(c, indent+2));\n  }\n  rec(tree.root, 0);\n  pre.textContent = lines.join(\"\\n\");\n  // allow clicking node ids by simple parsing: attach click handler to pre and map coordinates\n  // Instead of complex HTML, we'll detect click by asking for nodeId input manually (simple UI).\n}\n\n// Insert single key\ndocument.getElementById('insertBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('insertKey').value.trim();\n  if(raw===''){ log(\"Insert aborted: empty key\"); return; }\n  const key = raw;\n  pushHistory(\"before insert \"+key);\n  try {\n    tree.insert(key, false);\n    log(\"Inserted key: \"+key);\n    renderTree();\n  } catch(e){\n    log(\"Insert error: \"+e.message);\n  }\n});\n\n// Insert with step mode\ndocument.getElementById('insertStepBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('insertKey').value.trim();\n  if(raw===''){ log(\"Insert aborted: empty key\"); return; }\n  const key = raw;\n  pushHistory(\"before insert \"+key);\n  currentSteps = tree.insert(key, true);\n  currentStepIndex = -1;\n  log(\"Generated \"+currentSteps.length+\" steps for insertion of \"+key);\n  stepNext();\n});\n\n// Delete single key\ndocument.getElementById('deleteBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('deleteKey').value.trim();\n  if(raw===''){ log(\"Delete aborted: empty key\"); return; }\n  const key = raw;\n  pushHistory(\"before delete \"+key);\n  try {\n    tree.delete(key, false);\n    log(\"Deleted key: \"+key);\n    renderTree();\n  } catch(e){ log(\"Delete error: \"+e.message); }\n});\n\n// Delete with step mode\ndocument.getElementById('deleteStepBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('deleteKey').value.trim();\n  if(raw===''){ log(\"Delete aborted: empty key\"); return; }\n  const key = raw;\n  pushHistory(\"before delete \"+key);\n  currentSteps = tree.delete(key, true);\n  currentStepIndex = -1;\n  log(\"Generated \"+currentSteps.length+\" steps for deletion of \"+key);\n  stepNext();\n});\n\n// Search\ndocument.getElementById('searchBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('searchKey').value.trim();\n  if(raw===''){ log(\"Search aborted: empty key\"); return; }\n  const key = raw;\n  const res = tree.search(key);\n  if(res) {\n    log(\"Found key \"+key+\" in node id=\"+res.node.id+\" at index=\"+res.index);\n  } else {\n    log(\"Key \"+key+\" not found\");\n  }\n});\n\n// Bulk Insert\ndocument.getElementById('bulkInsertBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const raw = document.getElementById('bulkInsert').value.trim();\n  if(!raw){ log(\"Bulk insert aborted: no input\"); return; }\n  const parts = raw.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s!==\"\");\n  if(parts.length === 0){ log(\"No keys to insert\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before bulk insert\");\n  for(const p of parts){\n    tree.insert(p, false);\n  }\n  log(\"Bulk inserted \"+parts.length+\" keys\");\n  renderTree();\n});\n\n// Clear tree\ndocument.getElementById('clearBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  pushHistory(\"before clear\");\n  tree = new BTree(tree.t, tree.compare);\n  nextNodeId = 1;\n  renderTree();\n  log(\"Cleared tree\");\n});\n\n// Random inserts\ndocument.getElementById('randInsertBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const count = Math.max(1, parseInt(document.getElementById('randCount').value,10) || 10);\n  pushHistory(\"before random insert \"+count);\n  const keyType = document.getElementById('keyType').value;\n  for(let i=0;i<count;i++){\n    if(keyType === 'number'){\n      const v = Math.floor(Math.random()*1000);\n      tree.insert(String(v), false);\n    } else {\n      const v = 's'+Math.floor(Math.random()*10000);\n      tree.insert(v, false);\n    }\n  }\n  log(\"Inserted \"+count+\" random keys\");\n  renderTree();\n});\n\n// Range query\ndocument.getElementById('rangeBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const lowRaw = document.getElementById('rangeLow').value.trim();\n  const highRaw = document.getElementById('rangeHigh').value.trim();\n  const low = lowRaw === '' ? null : lowRaw;\n  const high = highRaw === '' ? null : highRaw;\n  const res = tree.rangeQuery(low, high);\n  log(\"Range query results (\"+(low||'-')+\" to \"+(high||'-')+\"): \"+res.join(\", \"));\n});\n\n// Traverse\ndocument.getElementById('traverseBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const arr=[];\n  tree.traverse(tree.root, arr);\n  log(\"In-order traversal: \"+arr.join(\", \"));\n});\n\n// Stepper controls\ndocument.getElementById('nextStep').addEventListener('click', stepNext);\ndocument.getElementById('prevStep').addEventListener('click', stepPrev);\ndocument.getElementById('resetSteps').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  currentSteps = null; currentStepIndex = -1; stopAutoplay(); log(\"Reset step session\");\n});\ndocument.getElementById('autoPlay').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  if(!currentSteps || currentSteps.length === 0){ log(\"No step session active\"); return; }\n  stopAutoplay();\n  autoplayTimer = setInterval(function(){\n    if(currentStepIndex >= currentSteps.length-1){ stopAutoplay(); return; }\n    stepNext();\n  }, Math.max(50, parseInt(document.getElementById('speed').value,10) || 600));\n  log(\"Autoplay started\");\n});\ndocument.getElementById('pausePlay').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  stopAutoplay();\n  log(\"Autoplay paused/stopped\");\n});\nfunction stopAutoplay(){\n  if(autoplayTimer) clearInterval(autoplayTimer);\n  autoplayTimer = null;\n}\n\nfunction stepNext(){\n  if(!currentSteps || currentSteps.length === 0){ log(\"No steps available\"); return; }\n  if(currentStepIndex < currentSteps.length-1){\n    currentStepIndex++;\n    const s = currentSteps[currentStepIndex];\n    if(s.snapshot) tree.fromJSON(s.snapshot);\n    renderTree();\n    log(\"Step \"+(currentStepIndex+1)+\"/\"+currentSteps.length+\": \"+s.message);\n  } else {\n    log(\"Already at last step\");\n  }\n}\n\nfunction stepPrev(){\n  if(!currentSteps || currentSteps.length === 0){ log(\"No steps available\"); return; }\n  if(currentStepIndex > 0){\n    currentStepIndex--;\n    const s = currentSteps[currentStepIndex];\n    if(s.snapshot) tree.fromJSON(s.snapshot);\n    renderTree();\n    log(\"Rewound to step \"+(currentStepIndex+1)+\"/\"+currentSteps.length+\": \"+s.message);\n  } else {\n    log(\"Already at first step\");\n  }\n}\n\n// Manual node operations\ndocument.getElementById('splitNodeBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  if(!nid){ log(\"Provide numeric Node ID\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before manual split of node \"+nid);\n  const res = tree.manualSplitNode(nid);\n  log(res.message || \"Manual split result: \"+JSON.stringify(res));\n  renderTree();\n});\n\ndocument.getElementById('mergeNodeBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  if(!nid){ log(\"Provide numeric Node ID\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before manual merge of node \"+nid);\n  const res = tree.manualMergeWithRight(nid);\n  log(res.message || \"Manual merge result: \"+JSON.stringify(res));\n  renderTree();\n});\n\ndocument.getElementById('borrowLeftBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  if(!nid){ log(\"Provide numeric Node ID\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before borrow-left of node \"+nid);\n  const res = tree.manualBorrowFromLeft(nid);\n  log(res.message || \"Borrow-left result: \"+JSON.stringify(res));\n  renderTree();\n});\n\ndocument.getElementById('borrowRightBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  if(!nid){ log(\"Provide numeric Node ID\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before borrow-right of node \"+nid);\n  const res = tree.manualBorrowFromRight(nid);\n  log(res.message || \"Borrow-right result: \"+JSON.stringify(res));\n  renderTree();\n});\n\n// Node editor open\ndocument.getElementById('editNodeBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  if(!nid){ log(\"Provide numeric Node ID\"); return; }\n  const node = tree.findNodeById(nid);\n  if(!node){ log(\"Node id \"+nid+\" not found\"); return; }\n  document.getElementById('nodeEditor').style.display = 'block';\n  document.getElementById('nodeKeys').value = node.keys.join(\", \");\n  document.getElementById('nodeChildren').value = node.children.map(c=>c.id).join(\", \");\n  document.getElementById('nodeLeaf').checked = node.leaf;\n  log(\"Opened editor for node id=\"+nid);\n});\n\n// Apply node edit\ndocument.getElementById('applyNodeEdit').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const nid = parseInt(document.getElementById('nodeIdInput').value,10);\n  const node = tree.findNodeById(nid);\n  if(!node){ log(\"Node id \"+nid+\" not found\"); return; }\n  pushHistory(\"before node edit \"+nid);\n  const keysRaw = document.getElementById('nodeKeys').value.trim();\n  node.keys = keysRaw === \"\" ? [] : keysRaw.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s!==\"\");\n  const childIds = document.getElementById('nodeChildren').value.trim();\n  if(childIds === \"\") node.children = [];\n  else {\n    const ids = childIds.split(',').map(s=>parseInt(s.trim(),10)).filter(n=>!isNaN(n));\n    const newChildren = [];\n    ids.forEach(id => {\n      const c = tree.findNodeById(id);\n      if(c) newChildren.push(c);\n      else log(\"Warning: child id \"+id+\" not found\");\n    });\n    node.children = newChildren;\n  }\n  node.leaf = document.getElementById('nodeLeaf').checked;\n  document.getElementById('nodeEditor').style.display = 'none';\n  log(\"Applied edits to node id=\"+nid);\n  renderTree();\n});\n\n// Close editor\ndocument.getElementById('closeNodeEditor').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  document.getElementById('nodeEditor').style.display = 'none';\n});\n\n// Export & Import\ndocument.getElementById('exportBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const txt = tree.toJSON();\n  // Show in an alertish prompt; copying to clipboard if available\n  try {\n    navigator.clipboard.writeText(txt).then(() => {\n      log(\"Exported JSON copied to clipboard. (Also printed below)\");\n      alert(\"JSON copied to clipboard. Also shown in a prompt (OK to close).\");\n      // show the JSON in prompt (not ideal but minimal UI)\n      window.open().document.write(\"<pre>\"+escapeHtml(txt)+\"</pre>\");\n    }, () => {\n      log(\"Clipboard write failed; showing JSON in new window.\");\n      window.open().document.write(\"<pre>\"+escapeHtml(txt)+\"</pre>\");\n    });\n  } catch(e){\n    window.open().document.write(\"<pre>\"+escapeHtml(txt)+\"</pre>\");\n  }\n});\n\nfunction escapeHtml(s){ return (s+\"\").replace(/&/g,\"&amp;\").replace(/</g,\"&lt;\").replace(/>/g,\"&gt;\"); }\n\ndocument.getElementById('importBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const txt = prompt(\"Paste JSON to import (this will replace current tree):\");\n  if(!txt) { log(\"Import aborted\"); return; }\n  try {\n    const obj = JSON.parse(txt);\n    pushHistory(\"before import JSON\");\n    tree.fromJSON(obj);\n    log(\"Imported tree from JSON\");\n    renderTree();\n  } catch(e){\n    log(\"Import failed: \"+e.message);\n  }\n});\n\n// File input import\ndocument.getElementById('importArea').addEventListener('change', function(e){\n  const f = e.target.files[0];\n  if(!f) return;\n  const reader = new FileReader();\n  reader.onload = function(ev){\n    try {\n      const obj = JSON.parse(ev.target.result);\n      pushHistory(\"before file import\");\n      tree.fromJSON(obj);\n      log(\"Imported tree from file: \"+f.name);\n      renderTree();\n    } catch(err){\n      log(\"File import error: \"+err.message);\n    }\n  };\n  reader.readAsText(f);\n});\n\n// Undo / Redo\ndocument.getElementById('undoBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  if(history.length === 0) { log(\"Nothing to undo\"); return; }\n  const snapshot = history.pop();\n  future.push(tree.cloneStructure());\n  restoreSnapshot(snapshot);\n  renderTree();\n  log(\"Undo applied\");\n  document.getElementById('redoBtn').disabled = false;\n});\n\ndocument.getElementById('redoBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  if(future.length === 0){ log(\"Nothing to redo\"); return; }\n  const snapshot = future.pop();\n  history.push(tree.cloneStructure());\n  restoreSnapshot(snapshot);\n  renderTree();\n  log(\"Redo applied\");\n  document.getElementById('undoBtn').disabled = false;\n});\n\n// Validate\ndocument.getElementById('validateBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const issues = tree.validate();\n  if(issues.length === 0) log(\"Validation passed: no issues found\");\n  else {\n    log(\"Validation found \"+issues.length+\" issues:\");\n    issues.forEach(i => log(\" - \" + i));\n  }\n});\n\n// Stats\ndocument.getElementById('statsBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const st = tree.stats();\n  log(\"Stats: nodes=\"+st.nodes+\" keys=\"+st.keys+\" leafCount=\"+st.leafCount+\" t=\"+st.t);\n});\n\n// Compact\ndocument.getElementById('compactBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  pushHistory(\"before compact/rebuild\");\n  tree.rebuild();\n  log(\"Rebuilt/compacted tree by reinserting all keys\");\n  renderTree();\n});\n\n// Disk pages\ndocument.getElementById('showPagesBtn').addEventListener('click', function(){\n  const pages = tree.diskPages();\n  log(\"Simulated disk pages (one node per page): count=\"+pages.length);\n  pages.forEach(p => log(\"Page \"+p.pageId+\": nodeid=\"+p.node.nodeId+\" keys=[\"+p.node.keys.join(\", \")+\"] leaf=\"+p.node.leaf));\n});\n\n// Utilities on load\nupdateConfigurationUI();\nrenderTree();\nlog(\"B-Tree demo loaded. Configure and interact using the controls.\");\n\n// Provide keyboard shortcut: Enter in various input fields triggers associated buttons\ndocument.getElementById('insertKey').addEventListener('keydown', function(e){ if(e.key==='Enter') document.getElementById('insertBtn').click(); });\ndocument.getElementById('deleteKey').addEventListener('keydown', function(e){ if(e.key==='Enter') document.getElementById('deleteBtn').click(); });\ndocument.getElementById('searchKey').addEventListener('keydown', function(e){ if(e.key==='Enter') document.getElementById('searchBtn').click(); });\n\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
